Skeleton.
(
Figs 75d–f
) As usual, there is a cortical skeleton of triactines (
Fig. 75e
), an inarticulated choanosomal skeleton (
Fig. 75d
) formed by the longer paired actine of subectosomal triactines and the unpaired actines of subatrial triactines, and an atrial skeleton (
Fig. 75f
) of tangential triactines. Rare diactines and trichoxeas.
